184
00:15:15,165 --> 00:15:16,374
Exactly.

185
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:20,629
It's a bad time for newspapers,
as you all know.

186
00:15:20,796 --> 00:15:26,343
The news hole is shrinking
as advertising dollars continue to decline.

187
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:31,640
Our circulation numbers are also down
as we compete with a variety of media.

188
00:15:32,015 --> 00:15:35,018
Technology is driving distribution...

189
00:15:36,394 --> 00:15:41,191
And the Internet is a free source
of news and opinions.

190
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:45,362
Seeking a balance in this new world,

191
00:15:45,487 --> 00:15:48,240
we're now faced with hard choices.

192
00:15:48,323 --> 00:15:52,744
We opened our first foreign bureau
in London in 1924.

193
00:15:53,036 --> 00:15:58,166
The sun's foreign coverage
has been a source of pride ever since.

194
00:16:00,043 --> 00:16:02,087
So it is with...

195
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,548
Tremendous regret...

196
00:16:05,799 --> 00:16:11,388
That I tell you that Chicago has made
it clear that the bureaus in Beijing,

197
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:15,892
Moscow, Jerusalem,
Johannesburg and London

198
00:16:16,184 --> 00:16:18,145
